To achieve this, we will use the AWS provider to create a VPC with private subnets across two Availability Zones. We will then provision an Elastic File System (EFS) with mount targets in those subnets. Finally, we will launch two EC2 instances using the latest Amazon Linux 2 AMI, ensuring they have the necessary Security Group rules to communicate with the EFS over port 2049.

