To link an existing ElastiCache user to an existing ElastiCache user group in AWS, you use the `aws_elasticache_user_group_association` resource. This resource manages the membership between the two entities.

Here is the Terraform configuration:

```hcl
# Define the provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# 1. Reference the existing ElastiCache User
# We use a data source to fetch the user by their ID
data "aws_elasticache_user" "existing_user" {
  user_id = "my-existing-user-id"
}

# 2. Reference the existing ElastiCache User Group
# We use a data source to fetch the group by its ID
data "aws_elasticache_user_group" "existing_group" {
  user_group_id = "my-existing-group-id"
}

# 3. Create the association between the user and the group
# This resource links the two existing entities together
resource "aws_elasticache_user_group_association" "example" {
  user_group_id = data.aws_elasticache_user_group.existing_group.user_group_id
  user_id       = data.aws_elasticache_user.existing_user.user_id
}
```

