To provision an Amazon DAX (DynamoDB Accelerator) cluster, we need to define several components: an IAM role that allows the DAX service to interact with DynamoDB, a subnet group to specify where the nodes reside, a security group to control access, and finally the cluster itself.

```hcl
# Configure the AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# 1. IAM Role for DAX service
resource "aws_iam_role" "dax_role" {
  name = "DAXServiceRole"

  assume_role_policy = jsonencode({
