To create a personalized Amazon DynamoDB Accelerator (DAX) Parameter Group, we need to define the `aws_dax_parameter_group` resource. This allows you to override default engine parameters (such as TTL settings) to suit your specific application requirements.

In the configuration below, I have defined a provider, a custom parameter group with modified query and record TTLs, and a placeholder for the DAX cluster itself to show how the parameter group is applied.

```hcl
# Terraform configuration for a personalized DAX Parameter Group

provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

# 1. Define the custom DAX Parameter Group
# This acts as the "category" of settings for your DAX cluster
resource "aws_dax_parameter_group" "personalized_dax_params" {
  name         = "personalized-dax-parameters"
  description = "Custom parameter group for optimizing cache TTLs"

  # Adjusting the Query TTL (Time to Live for query results)
  # Default is often 300000ms (5 minutes)
  parameters {
    name  = "query-ttl-millis"
    value = "600000" # Increase to 10 minutes
  }

  # Adjusting the Record TTL (Time to Live for individual items)
  parameters {
    name  = "record-ttl-millis"
    value = "120000" # Decrease to 2 minutes for more frequent updates
  }
}

# 2. Example DAX Cluster application
# This demonstrates how to associate the parameter group created above
resource "aws_dax_cluster" "example" {
  cluster_name       = "my-dax-cluster"
  iam_role_arn       = aws_iam_role.dax_role.arn
  node_type          = "dax.r4.large"
  replication_factor = 1

  # Linking the personalized parameter group
  parameter_group_name = aws_dax_parameter_group.personalized_dax_params.name

  # Note: Subnet group and Security group IDs are required for a functional cluster
  subnet_group_name  = "my-dax-subnet-group"
