To implement a scheduled backup for an EC2 instance, we need to define the EC2 instance, an AWS Backup Vault to store the recovery points, a Backup Plan with a daily schedule (cron), and a Backup Selection that targets the instance using tags. We also need an IAM role that allows the AWS Backup service to perform operations on our behalf.

```hcl
# Configure the AWS Provider
